Description: Fragment of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Oval handle. Rectangular stamp with caduceus symbol. Clay fine pink-buff; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Drawn by Petrie (Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p.55, 11). Name Drakontidas. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, CEALEX CRI 031.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0948)
